rComments: As a CBC I always felt a divide between my ethnic and Canadian identities somewhat feeling I don't truly belong to either group. Blessed to have a positive role model who helped me realize I don't need to choose -I can be both because I am both. This realization lifted a big burden off my shoulders.

Incredible! Almost 5 years since I finished Stats.. other profs don't remember me after 1 semester lol. Ill never forget the life lessons he taught me. Thanks to his mentorship I secured admissions to Columbia & Cornell and waitlisted at Brown. Excited, terrified, proud, thankful to be the first in my family to go to Grad School!
the best prop i ever have

Intellectually rewarding and challenging course. We learned how risk management can be applied to different type of enterprises. Visiting Directors and VPs to learn more about their risk management practices was a big highlight. I admired how Lucas encouraged us to creatively find better answers to solve the same problems with subsequent tries.
Could be a stand up comedian and yes, very cute! Midterm was somewhat tough but he clarified wording and phrasing issues.
Good with explaining complex concepts using easy-to-understand examples

Really great experience doing my Project Management research thesis with Professor Thung. Good balance of independent work and supervision & mentorship. I really like the clear timelines of when outline, drafts, final papers are due. Rich feedback encouraged me to think creatively and I made connecctions  with 1 Sr Manager for a paid internship

rComments: He was a professor that is care of his students' work. When I have any questions about the course, he is willing to answer my question . Also, before and after the class, he also stay and help other students to fix the problem that they face in their assignment. He also has a lot of interaction in class with student.

Blended course, amazing lectures and awesome field project with golden opportunities to connect with industry experts. The online part involved quite a bit of reading but they're useful. I learned a lot because I worked hard. Lucas helped improve my writing and communication. He created a fun, creative and  positive learning environment.

Extremely useful course on Career Strategies! Classes divided into seminars, workshops, discussions. Brilliant and inspirational professor with wealth of industry experience. Group project helped me network with a wide range of companies and one hired me full time! Lucas provided very generous guidance during interviews and salary negotiations

You won't find too many UofT professors who have the combined intelligence, personality and humour as Professor Thung. He is a man of his word who is generous with his time. I was given several glowing references for my graduate school applications. Easily the best Professor I have had the pleasure of knowing.

Energetic + funny + engaging. Lucas cares about his students and takes time to get to know us. Not sure how he knows our names though since it's a big class. I started as a shy student and ended up participating quite often after being encouraged to talk more. Medium term tests + very difficult final but we were given plenty hints. Participate^10!
